recording studio, almost exactly the same way they said it when they were 
on set filming. They have the luxury of going back and watching the footage 
to make sure an actor says it the exact same way. And they have the luxury 
of getting an actor to give multiple takes if they need to. In the case of 
the Bad Lip Reading videos, some of the techniques used are the same when 
it comes to the editing, but the process in which it gets done, is still 
very different and a lot more tedious. It's probably why there is 
incredibly long periods of time before they upload a new video. I'm sure 
they go through hundreds of hours worth of footage, trying to find the 
perfect clips. There's lots of L cutting to mask certain parts of the 
video. And then there is the actual syncing process which I can imagine 
takes another hundred hours or so of tweaking and fine tuning. Lets not 
forget the fact that they have to come up with clever stuff to say for all 
of these clips. ADR with films is reciting lines that are scripted and 
filmed already.
